
how to include your css in html :

    css stand for styling your element of the web page for example
    this goes from this 

    <h1>this is a test</h1>
    to
    <h1 style="color: blue; text-align: center">this is a test</h1>

    this is directly in a tag put as attribute

    i you want to apply it on multiple tag you can put itr in the header
    <head>
        <style>
        h1 { 
            color: blue; 
            text-align: center;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    this is put as a list of attribute affecting only h1


    and the last option you can reference it so you can reapply it whenever you want to 
    two separate file
    <head>
        <link rel="styleSheet"; href="csscourse.css";> 
    </head>
    here rel stand for relationship and href the actual link of the file 
    in ccs file :
    h1{
        color: blue;
    }


