now how to select your tag that get associated to cssattribute you can either 
    write :

    only <th></th>
    h1 {
        color: blue;
    }  

    <h1></h1> and <h2></h2>
    h1, h2 {
        color: blue;
    }  

   or you can add a class attribute to your h1 so all the h1 are not taken 

   in html:
   <h1>heading 1</h1>
   <h1>heading 2</h1>
   <h1 class="headingBlue">heading 3</h1>
   <h1 class="headingBlue">heading 4</h1>

   in css :
   .headingBlue {
        color: blue;
   }
    and if you want only one to be selected use the attribute id

   in html:
   <h1>heading 1</h1>
   <h1 id="headingOrange">heading 2</h1>
   <h1 class="headingBlue">heading 3</h1>
   <h1 class="headingBlue">heading 4</h1>
   
   in css :
   .headingBlue {
        color: blue;
   }

   #headingOrange {
        color: blue;
   }

